news.title: Nexus Select Trust's net profit up 36.97% quarter-on-quarter in Q4 FY24
news.para: Nexus Select Trust's net consolidated total income stood at 5,607.02 million in Q4 FY24, a quarter-on-quarter dip of 4.71 per cent from Rs 5,884.02 million it recorded in Q3 FY24.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body makes structural audit mandatory for 30-year-old buildings
news.para: Concerned civic officials have been instructed to issue notices under 265A of the Maharashtra Municipal Corporation Act (MMCA), to the structures of 30-year-old for conducting structural audits compulsorily in time bound manner.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC collects a sum of Rs 3,905 crores as property tax so far
news.para: Meanwhile, municipal commissioner Bhushan Gagrani has directed the civic administration to speed up the process of auctioning seized assets of big property tax defaulters, who have defaulted on payment for years.

news.title: Bengaluru: Mantri Square mall sealed over Rs 50 crore tax dues
news.para: BBMP has sealed the mall multiple times over the past few years - the last time was on March 16, just a few hours before announcement of Lok Sabha elections.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance IPO subscribed 25.49 times on final day
news.para: The Rs 3,000 crore initial share-sale received bids for 1,78,65,45,247 shares against 7,00,89,373 shares on offer, according to data available with the NSE.

news.title: DMart buys land in Mumbai's Chandivali for Rs 117 crore
news.para: The billionaire Radhakishan Damani-promoted company has paid a stamp duty of Rs 7.03 crore for the transaction that was registered on May 6, according to documents accessed through real estate data analysis platform CRE Matrix.

news.title: Housing construction firms in Germany fall short on orders: Survey
news.para: In April, 55.2% of companies reported a lack of orders, down slightly from 56.2% the previous month, said the Ifo economic institute, Housebuilders are looking for signs of hope, but there's no end to the crisis in sight," said Klaus Wohlrabe, Ifo's head of surveys.

news.title: Gera Developments invests over Rs 1,425 crore in Pune project
news.para: Rohit Gera, managing director of Gera Developments said, "The company has invested about Rs 325 crore in acquiring the land parcel and the construction cost is about Rs 1,100 crore."

news.title: Residents oppose Bengaluru development body's plan to redevelop complexes
news.para: The controversial move, initially proposed in 2018, was put on hold due to reasons, including changes of governments, the Covid pandemic, and strong opposition from Resident Welfare Associations (RWAs).

news.title: Hyderabad: RIZE Constructions' owner, four others arrested in wall collapse incident
news.para: Among others arrested are Murugesan Sathish Kumar, the Site Engineer, Mariya Francis Xavier Raj, the Project Manager, and Dhadiyala Rajesh and Allu Ram Reddy, both contractors.

news.title: Ajmera Realty's net profit up 90.40% in Q4 FY24
news.para: Ajmera Realty's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 234.08 crore in Q4 FY24, a growth of 98.71 per cent from Rs 117.80 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Asian Paints' net profit up 1.34% in Q4 FY24
news.para: Asian Paints' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 8,917.87 crore in Q4 FY24, a minor growth of 0.28 per cent from Rs 8,892.82 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Sebi proposes measures to reduce compliance burden on REITs and InvITs
news.para: Markets regulator Sebi on Thursday proposed to drastically reduce the trading lot size of privately placed infrastructure investment trusts (InvITs) to Rs 25 lakh in a bid to boost investors' participation and increase liquidity of such investment vehicles.

news.title: Home First Finance eyes $75 million fundraise from US DFC
news.para: Home First Finance aims to raise $75 million through ECB from US DFC to support 30% business growth in FY25. The company plans to diversify borrowing sources, expand distribution network, and focus on emerging affordable housing markets.

news.title: Piramal Capital & Housing invests Rs 300 crore in Cybercity Builders' Hyderabad project
news.para: Piramal Capital & Housing Finance has invested nearly ₹300 crore in a villa development project by Cybercity Builders & Developers in Hyderabad. The funding will also be used to acquire land Cybercity Developers bought from Phoenix Group.

news.title: About 20 builders involved in stalled projects have paid 25% dues: Noida Authority
news.para: Four builders have deposited 25 per cent of the total amount of Rs 83.47 crore and partial amount of Rs 53.68 crore. Thus, the authority received a total of Rs 224.45 crore till May 9, 2024," it said in a statement.

news.title: Customer satisfaction, safety is top priority for us: Harsh Jagwani, MD, Notandas Realty
news.para: In this exclusive tete-a-tete, Harsh Jagwani, Managing Director of Notandas Realty, underscores the importance of safety norms on project sites to ensure the well-being of both workers and residents.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance IPO subscribed 1.48 times on day two of offer
news.para: Among investors' category, Qualified Institutional Buyers (QIBs) portion received 2.05 times subscription while the quota for non-institutional investors got subscribed 1.94 times. The Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) part received 94 per cent subscription.

news.title: Delhi HC asks NBCC to return Rs 76 lakh with interest to homebuyer
news.para: The petitioner, a retired government employee, said he purchased the flat in 'NBCC Green View Apartments', a project launched in 2012 for Gurugram, but in spite of paying the entire sale price of over Rs 76 lakh in 2017, the unit was never handed over to him.

news.title: China's Country Garden aims to pay missed coupons by next week
news.para: Country Garden, which defaulted on its $11 billion of offshore bonds and extended other onshore bond repayments late last year, said in a filing it was unable to pay onshore coupons due on Thursday, though it was still trying to raise funds.
